01:47:34.920 --> 01:47:38.720
[Guest]: daughter would never get the justice and she didn't get him by the way the father

01:47:38.720 --> 01:47:43.600
[Guest]: was acquitted but why would all these details be there on the internet it's

01:47:43.600 --> 01:47:47.800
[Guest]: not fair to her so that violent times now it's in my perspective of this

01:47:47.800 --> 01:47:53.240
[Guest]: pursuit for justice change that the person who wants justice is the person

01:47:53.240 --> 01:47:56.840
[Guest]: who should control the narrative is something which I decided even then and

01:47:56.840 --> 01:48:01.960
[Guest]: then this this 2016 story about this Manju warrior also made me realize that

01:48:01.960 --> 01:48:05.880
[Guest]: look we need to start telling stories differently we are always saying this

01:48:05.880 --> 01:48:12.160
[Guest]: from the male gaze and it starts from even the most local crime story right

01:48:12.160 --> 01:48:15.480
[Guest]: you there's another instance I have a I had a colleague called Priyanka

01:48:15.480 --> 01:48:19.600
[Guest]: Thirumurthy she used to work in Tamil Nadu Bureau so there was a story about a

01:48:19.600 --> 01:48:24.380
[Guest]: man getting killed on the first night and the headline said that the woman

01:48:24.380 --> 01:48:29.080
[Guest]: kills the hubby because he's not handsome so I told Priyanka that called

01:48:29.080 --> 01:48:34.160
[Guest]: a station and check on the story now why did that person if this the story came

01:48:34.160 --> 01:48:37.880
[Guest]: in all the newspapers okay because it is an agency copy why because the reporter

01:48:37.880 --> 01:48:41.720
[Guest]: would have called up the station and said what is the FIR the FIR is based on

01:48:41.720 --> 01:48:46.280
[Guest]: the complaint given by the man the dead man's family which says he is ugly she

01:48:46.280 --> 01:48:50.480
[Guest]: didn't like him so she killed him crime reporter does not put any brain writes

01:48:50.480 --> 01:48:54.040
[Guest]: a story I don't Priyanka you called a station I did not give her any any

01:48:54.040 --> 01:48:58.760
[Guest]: instructions but she called me back and said ma'am I asked them what did the

01:48:58.760 --> 01:49:03.400
[Guest]: woman say and they said that the woman did not want to get married her parents

01:49:03.400 --> 01:49:07.120
[Guest]: forced her to get married and in the first night when he tried to have sex

01:49:07.120 --> 01:49:11.680
[Guest]: with her she she in a fit of whatever tension rage whatever killed that's her

01:49:11.680 --> 01:49:16.600
[Guest]: version which may be true may not be dude but point is Priyanka had that had

01:49:16.600 --> 01:49:20.440
[Guest]: that sense to ask what is the woman's version she was not thinking like a

01:49:20.440 --> 01:49:25.280
[Guest]: crime reporter and then I realized that when you're a woman reporter in your

01:49:25.280 --> 01:49:28.600
[Guest]: newsroom and you have someone who's a Dalit or a Muslim or from the LGBT

01:49:28.600 --> 01:49:31.960
[Guest]: community I'm not saying that a woman has to report only on women's issues or

01:49:31.960 --> 01:49:35.160
[Guest]: a Dalit person or somebody from the community should report only in the

01:49:35.160 --> 01:49:40.000
[Guest]: community but they bring a certain sense to the newsroom which is why if you are

01:49:40.000 --> 01:49:44.040
[Guest]: women in all levels of decision-making they bring that change to your

01:49:44.040 --> 01:49:49.320
[Guest]: organization and organizations have to invest in this they cannot say that oh

01:49:49.320 --> 01:49:52.240
[Guest]: my god inclusivity is not something I can really target because I'd look at

01:49:52.240 --> 01:49:57.480
[Guest]: merit you look at merit also but you this has to be in your vision otherwise

01:49:57.480 --> 01:50:00.960
[Guest]: your organization will not speak all voices so for me in the beginning it was

01:50:00.960 --> 01:50:05.840
[Guest]: only about the feminist viewpoint you know telling a story from not a male

01:50:05.840 --> 01:50:11.360
[Guest]: gaze and we put all our energy into it and it really worked I feel like we have

01:50:11.360 --> 01:50:16.080
[Guest]: been able to make a lot of changes for example people who watch Tamil movies

01:50:16.080 --> 01:50:21.800
[Guest]: they must be knowing that a few years ago every big movie had the hero stalking

01:50:21.800 --> 01:50:26.600
[Guest]: the heroine stalking singing stalking singing it has stopped to a large extent

01:50:26.600 --> 01:50:30.240
[Guest]: now like an actor like Dhanush half his movies were like that he doesn't act

01:50:30.240 --> 01:50:34.360
[Guest]: like that anymore because of the criticism and I'm very happy that as an

01:50:34.360 --> 01:50:38.280
[Guest]: ordinary writers like Anna Wettekar where the news minute wrote first about

01:50:38.280 --> 01:50:43.480
[Guest]: these things very very powerfully I still remember the wife of one of these

01:50:43.480 --> 01:50:47.040
[Guest]: top actors calling me and saying I will watch out for his scripts from now and

01:50:47.040 --> 01:50:52.080
[Guest]: today you can see that effort of you know Anna or Sowmya and so many others

01:50:52.080 --> 01:50:56.080
[Guest]: continuously writing about it there is a change right in the film industry and

01:50:56.080 --> 01:51:00.400
[Guest]: when we wrote that first article it was there was this girl called Swati who was

01:51:00.400 --> 01:51:04.600
[Guest]: murdered in the in the in a railway station in Chennai we wrote about the

01:51:04.600 --> 01:51:08.440
[Guest]: fact that Tamil movies should not have stalking scenes they'll come with his

01:51:08.440 --> 01:51:12.600
[Guest]: Arival which is a sword so we wrote that this kind of valorizing the hero this

01:51:12.600 --> 01:51:19.160
[Guest]: toxic masculinity is not correct we face such a backlash one of the biggest most

01:51:19.160 --> 01:51:24.000
[Guest]: respected reviewers actually wrote a piece in one of the newspapers saying

01:51:24.000 --> 01:51:26.880
[Guest]: that there is no empirical data to prove that people follow what they see in

01:51:26.880 --> 01:51:32.840
[Guest]: movies but once we started the trend more and more I mean they were already

01:51:32.840 --> 01:51:36.760
[Guest]: writers who are writing this but as an organization nobody was following it

01:51:36.760 --> 01:51:41.760
[Guest]: right see you can have a writer in the Times of India one review will look at a

01:51:41.760 --> 01:51:47.200
[Guest]: movie in a certain way but we made sure that news minute or any review looks at

01:51:47.200 --> 01:51:51.040
[Guest]: the movie in a certain way in a feminist viewpoint and we wrote more and more

01:51:51.040 --> 01:51:55.560
[Guest]: about it we were getting thrashed left right and center but we didn't stop and

01:51:55.560 --> 01:51:59.360
[Guest]: today I believe that all those people along with us in all those organizations

01:51:59.360 --> 01:52:03.600
[Guest]: have really ushered in that change it's not like the film industry woke up one

01:52:03.600 --> 01:52:06.800
[Guest]: day and decided I will not write stalking movies it's because society

01:52:06.800 --> 01:52:12.680
[Guest]: reacted the media reacted so that way I feel that we need more and more women

01:52:12.680 --> 01:52:17.160
[Amit Varma]: and that will definitely bring in more change yeah so I have a couple of

01:52:17.160 --> 01:52:20.680
[Amit Varma]: further digressions from this digression so I hope we eventually managed to get

01:52:20.680 --> 01:52:24.760
[Guest]: back to where I was going I have been diverting your attention too much right

01:52:24.760 --> 01:52:29.000
[Amit Varma]: no because you you're just so full of so much knowledge and great insights that

01:52:29.000 --> 01:52:33.680
[Amit Varma]: I'm just like overwhelmed but so we'll take one of those digressions before we

01:52:33.680 --> 01:52:37.120
[Amit Varma]: go into the break which is one of the best books I've read in the last decade

01:52:37.120 --> 01:52:41.640
[Amit Varma]: is this book by supil Tetlock called super forecasting and one of the

01:52:41.640 --> 01:52:45.120
[Amit Varma]: sideways insights in that the book is not about that but one of the sideways

01:52:45.120 --> 01:52:50.280
[Amit Varma]: insights in that it was about the study we showed that the best factor in

01:52:50.280 --> 01:52:53.920
[Amit Varma]: decision-making when you think about the quality of decision-making the most

01:52:53.920 --> 01:52:59.520
[Amit Varma]: important factor is not intelligence or education it is diversity the more

01:52:59.520 --> 01:53:03.400
[Amit Varma]: diverse a group of people the better the decision that you will get in fact

01:53:03.400 --> 01:53:07.320
[Amit Varma]: therefore I would say that the route to merit is actually through diversity

01:53:07.320 --> 01:53:12.040
[Amit Varma]: that's where it comes from and one example of that of course is that you

01:53:12.040 --> 01:53:15.000
[Amit Varma]: know the story of the woman who killed her husband that you managed to get

01:53:15.000 --> 01:53:20.960
[Amit Varma]: another point of view to deepen the you know and make the readers appreciation

01:53:20.960 --> 01:53:24.940
[Amit Varma]: of that story richer because you had a diverse reporter because you had a woman

01:53:24.940 --> 01:53:27.920
[Amit Varma]: who could look at it from the woman's point of view and similarly for other

01:53:27.920 --> 01:53:32.560
[Amit Varma]: stories you'll have other points of view and other layers which you kind of cut

01:53:32.560 --> 01:53:36.040
[Amit Varma]: through and this is something you've also spoken about and I just think that

01:53:36.040 --> 01:53:39.840
[Amit Varma]: what editors should do like if I was running an organization my first

01:53:39.840 --> 01:53:43.440
[Amit Varma]: principle would always be that if there's a position and there are two

01:53:43.440 --> 01:53:47.440
[Amit Varma]: equal candidates you take the one who increases the diversity in whatever way

01:53:47.440 --> 01:53:52.160
[Amit Varma]: across whatever margin and this is something you've spoken about as well so

01:53:52.160 --> 01:53:55.440
[Amit Varma]: you know how do you think editors should approach this because I think many

01:53:55.440 --> 01:54:00.680
[Amit Varma]: editors wouldn't even be aware that this is a problem that we have this you you're

01:54:00.680 --> 01:54:04.800
[Amit Varma]: really hiring from the same pool of people everything is homogenous and in a

01:54:04.800 --> 01:54:10.400
[Amit Varma]: sense from 30 years ago it would be natural because you'd have your entire

01:54:10.400 --> 01:54:14.480
[Amit Varma]: talent pool coming from like st. Stephens in Delhi and Hindu in Delhi if

01:54:14.480 --> 01:54:18.880
[Amit Varma]: you're there everybody knows everybody else it's the same pool of people today

01:54:18.880 --> 01:54:23.400
[Amit Varma]: that pool of people is everybody I mean not everybody but way more people have

01:54:23.400 --> 01:54:27.160
[Amit Varma]: access to technology are exposed to the world have points of view and whatever

01:54:27.160 --> 01:54:31.080
[Amit Varma]: so as an editor what would you advise to other editors be how should they

01:54:31.080 --> 01:54:37.280
[Guest]: approach this see I am NOT from St. Stephens or the Hindu or any college in

01:54:37.280 --> 01:54:39.880
[Guest]: Delhi or Bombay I like I said I studied in government Victoria College in

01:54:39.880 --> 01:54:44.880
[Guest]: Palakkad so if I I then bring a different perspective to the newsroom right which

01:54:44.880 --> 01:54:49.300
[Guest]: others didn't so that way every person has to be looked at like that I have

01:54:49.300 --> 01:54:54.200
[Guest]: vacancy now in Karnataka and Tamil Nadu bureaus and a lot of male reporters are

01:54:54.200 --> 01:54:57.400
[Guest]: there who have sent their resumes they are very talented I'm not saying they

01:54:57.400 --> 01:55:01.520
[Guest]: are not in fact some of them align with what our organization wants very well

01:55:01.520 --> 01:55:06.360
[Guest]: but we already have two male reporter one male reporter Prajwal in Karnataka

01:55:06.360 --> 01:55:11.760
[Guest]: and we have Shabbir who's joining us in Tamil Nadu so I'm very clear how much

01:55:11.760 --> 01:55:16.480
[Guest]: of a talented the resume from the male reporter is I don't want it now I want a

01:55:16.480 --> 01:55:20.000
[Guest]: female reporter there I'm not saying that Prajwal will not be sensitive to a

01:55:20.000 --> 01:55:24.760
[Guest]: issue dealing with women but he will not have the viewpoint of a woman right then

01:55:24.760 --> 01:55:30.880
[Guest]: my other question is I have to take a woman now in that itself I have to look

01:55:30.880 --> 01:55:35.500
[Guest]: at where did they grow up are they going to be same city bred same kind of vision

01:55:35.500 --> 01:55:38.960
[Guest]: they have had they come from a village or a two-tier city or whatever and

01:55:38.960 --> 01:55:42.920
[Guest]: they'll have a better perspective of things happening in the state what what

01:55:42.920 --> 01:55:46.440
[Guest]: is the community or caste or whatever or religion they belong to so these are all

01:55:46.440 --> 01:55:51.680
[Guest]: different things now everything cannot be boiled down and you know every time I

01:55:51.680 --> 01:55:55.160
[Guest]: cannot make that perfect choice but these are all thoughts going through our

01:55:55.160 --> 01:55:59.920
[Guest]: minds right that we want diversity I mean I'm not saying that every person we

01:55:59.920 --> 01:56:03.680
[Guest]: hire is to increase diversity in the newsroom or it does not end up like that

01:56:03.680 --> 01:56:07.560
[Guest]: because eventually I am also thinking oh my god I have to fill that vacancy I

01:56:07.560 --> 01:56:11.120
[Guest]: can't run the bureau with just Prajwal he it's too much work on him I have to

01:56:11.120 --> 01:56:16.160
[Guest]: have a second reporter and eventually maybe I will agree to one compromise but

01:56:16.160 --> 01:56:19.880
[Guest]: I'm not going to compromise on the fact that it is going to be a woman now which

01:56:19.880 --> 01:56:23.360
[Guest]: where is she going to come from what caste is she going to belong to those

01:56:23.360 --> 01:56:26.440
[Guest]: are compromise I may eventually make I don't know as of now I'm not recruited

01:56:26.440 --> 01:56:31.960
[Guest]: anyone but I am saying as an editor this should be in your thought you are not a

01:56:31.960 --> 01:56:36.000
[Guest]: newsroom if you have everybody thinking the same way everyone coming from the

01:56:36.000 --> 01:56:41.240
[Guest]: same privilege then there is no perspective I mean you have some decent

01:56:41.240 --> 01:56:44.280
[Guest]: progressive perspectives about everything but if you want to report

01:56:44.280 --> 01:56:48.360
[Guest]: about a political movement or if you want to report root causes of things

01:56:48.360 --> 01:56:52.440
[Guest]: like I have a reporter called Charan Teja he covers Andhra Pradesh and Telangana

01:56:52.440 --> 01:56:57.280
[Guest]: the stuff that he writes about OBC movements in Andhra how the BJP is

01:56:57.280 --> 01:57:01.400
[Guest]: trying to come into the you know OBC classes can take the votes away make

01:57:01.400 --> 01:57:05.160
[Guest]: sure that these smaller OBC organization join that's something that he can see on

01:57:05.160 --> 01:57:08.560
[Guest]: the ground on a daily basis and he understands it that my top-down vision

01:57:08.560 --> 01:57:13.680
[Guest]: from Bangalore right so it makes a whole lot of difference I'm not saying that it

01:57:13.680 --> 01:57:17.920
[Guest]: is possible for all news organizations do it all the time I understand there

01:57:17.920 --> 01:57:21.320
[Guest]: are a lot of issues because we sometimes do not get resumes we don't get the

01:57:21.320 --> 01:57:27.120
[Guest]: people we like but as much as possible the onus is on each of us to try and if

01:57:27.120 --> 01:57:32.120
[Guest]: we don't try then we cannot say you know it's not my business I know I know a

01:57:32.120 --> 01:57:36.920
[Guest]: news laundry was trying to do that survey about inclusivity and even how

01:57:36.920 --> 01:57:39.800
[Guest]: many women are there in the newsroom a lot of people did not want to talk to

01:57:39.800 --> 01:57:44.840
[Guest]: them in fact when they called me for the caste survey they asked like five or six

01:57:44.840 --> 01:57:49.200
[Guest]: really bad questions I mean the sense what is your name where do you come from

01:57:49.200 --> 01:57:53.680
[Guest]: some random questions they asked those are important ones but generally what I

01:57:53.680 --> 01:57:58.000
[Guest]: think about certain in the last question is what is your caste so I said boss

01:57:58.000 --> 01:58:01.440
[Guest]: this survey is about caste right I mean it's evident why don't you just ask me

01:58:01.440 --> 01:58:04.920
[Guest]: after the first three questions so he said no if I ask it first a lot of

01:58:04.920 --> 01:58:09.240
[Guest]: people don't want to reply so I want to warm them up and then I go to the last

01:58:09.240 --> 01:58:13.160
[Guest]: question that is how problematic it is people don't want to talk about their

01:58:13.160 --> 01:58:16.720
[Guest]: privilege and within the newsroom they don't want to change it now I don't have

01:58:16.720 --> 01:58:20.840
[Guest]: a perfect solution or I have changed the newsroom that dramatically I also wish

01:58:20.840 --> 01:58:27.360
[Guest]: to do more and in a newsroom of 40 people it's more difficult to do but if

01:58:27.360 --> 01:58:31.240
[Guest]: you are in a larger newsroom I think you do have the bandwidth to do it so if

01:58:31.240 --> 01:58:35.040
[Guest]: more editors think that way then we will see change no doubt I mean imagine if

01:58:35.040 --> 01:58:39.040
[Guest]: Times of India had all women editors for their website at some point of time

01:58:39.040 --> 01:58:43.560
[Guest]: somebody is going to say right stop these nonsensical clickbait articles

01:58:43.560 --> 01:58:48.000
[Guest]: which you have it is just degrading women I'm sure there will be some editor

01:58:48.000 --> 01:58:51.280
[Amit Varma]: who will say that and if she had three others support her. I know for a fact there are

01:58:51.280 --> 01:58:55.160
[Amit Varma]: women editors in the Times of India who have said that. No said that

01:58:55.160 --> 01:58:58.320
[Guest]: meaning they should be in a position to stop it that's what I'm saying it's not

01:58:58.320 --> 01:59:03.680
