[Amit Varma]: one of the things when I teach my writing course on my podcasting course

02:07:26.120 --> 02:07:30.120
[Amit Varma]: one of the things I keep kind of emphasizing on is that don't think of

02:07:30.120 --> 02:07:34.240
[Amit Varma]: yourself as tied down to this one thing that I write or I do this or I do that

02:07:34.240 --> 02:07:38.880
[Amit Varma]: you know you have things you want to express and you can express them in

02:07:38.880 --> 02:07:43.480
[Amit Varma]: multiple ways you can use your imagination in multiple ways and so on

02:07:43.480 --> 02:07:48.920
[Amit Varma]: and so forth and I and at some level even how we think of the media is

02:07:48.920 --> 02:07:53.960
[Amit Varma]: something that you know I've realized that we need to re-examine because you

02:07:53.960 --> 02:07:57.760
[Amit Varma]: know earlier you'll think that oh okay I'm maybe I'm a print journalist or

02:07:57.760 --> 02:08:01.400
[Amit Varma]: maybe I'm a TV journalist or whatever but there is one form and I box myself

02:08:01.400 --> 02:08:05.680
[Amit Varma]: into that but the truth is you know as people like you know in the digital

02:08:05.680 --> 02:08:11.800
[Amit Varma]: media that there are various ways to reach the reader the listener you know

02:08:11.800 --> 02:08:15.680
[Amit Varma]: the person out there who wants what you're giving and like I looked at your

02:08:15.680 --> 02:08:18.800
[Amit Varma]: Instagram and I quite liked it you know you might say you're not very active

02:08:18.800 --> 02:08:22.560
[Amit Varma]: there but I kind of liked it you're putting up snippets sometimes you put up

